<font color="#FF0000">REFLECTIONS</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 26 16:41:17 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
I could not agree with Doc Del more. This is a day to honor those who fell at arms.<br><br>
It is also a day for reflection by those who survived conflict. No greater honor can be paid the fallen than homage by those who survived.<br><br>
A Revolutionary War Soldier lies buried on my property. He lies forgotten by everyone. I have my own private and personal &quot;ceremony&quot; for this comrade in arms on Memorial Day and Veteran's Day. It matters to me not what convention is ascribed by society for the common bond between us all transcends time and space. I pay homage to those who fell befor, after, and beside me. In his time, this Revolutionary War Soldier, now at peace in his grave, did not do less.    
<p><code>-- art16@ix.netcom.com  (Arthur Varanelli) </code><p>


